# Custom Command Triggers
- When I type "/full-rebuild", execute the [Full Deployment Pipeline] defined below.
- if any error happens during the run, stop immediately and show me the error.

# [Full Deployment Pipeline]
Context: The project is in a WSL Safe Box (no /mnt). All paths are relative to ~/openclaw-project.

Step 1: Stop & Cleanup
- Execute: `./launch.sh stop`

Step 2: Update Code
- Execute: `git pull origin main`
- Note: If conflicts occur, ask to run `git reset --hard HEAD`.

Step 3: Clean & Rebuild Components
- Execute: `cargo clean`
- Execute: `cargo build --release -p hone-imessage`
- Execute: `cargo build --release -p hone-discord`
- Execute: `cargo build --release -p hone-feishu`
- Execute: `cargo build --release -p hone-telegram`

Step 4: Tauri Binary Prep
- Execute: `mkdir -p bins/hone-desktop/binaries`
- Copy and rename to target `x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu`:
  - `cp target/release/hone-imessage bins/hone-desktop/binaries/hone-imessage-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu`
  - `cp target/release/hone-discord bins/hone-desktop/binaries/hone-discord-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu`
  - `cp target/release/hone-feishu bins/hone-desktop/binaries/hone-feishu-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu`
  - `cp target/release/hone-telegram bins/hone-desktop/binaries/hone-telegram-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu`

Step 5: System Verification & Launch
- Execute: `./target/release/hone-cli doctor`

Step 6: Finalize
- Notify me that the system is built, verified